(:kind :chapter :book "Lacuna Labs Doc" :chapter-number null :title "Sakura Scheme — Completeness + Discipline Audit" :source-path "/Users/alfred/code/lacuna-labs/research/curator/specs/SAKURA-SCHEME-COMPLETENESS-AUDIT.md" :size 25571 :sha256 "aadc0b9d15659d70" :content "# Sakura Scheme — Completeness + Discipline Audit\n\n> **Status:** audit · 2026-06-09 · architect pass · read-only inventory\n> **Scope:** every verb Sakura can speak (`paint-*`, scene, card, motion, camera, audio, podcast, conway, layout, widget, base, cart-prelude) plus the Paint Kit, the cart corpus (270 `.sks` files), and the on-disk manual.\n> **Reference:** [`curator-web/docs/SCHEME-INVENTORY.md`](../../curator-web/docs/SCHEME-INVENTORY.md) (deep audit, 2026-06-08) is the source for line-cites; this doc is the architect-tier roll-up + drift table + next-corpus punch list.\n\n---\n\n## §0. Headline numbers\n\n| Population | Count |\n|---|---|\n| Total verbs installed across all installers | **370** |\n| of which: base.js (math/list/string/predicate/iter) | 117 |\n| of which: paint kit primitives (`paint-*`) | 29 |\n| of which: card verbs (`card-*`, `cards-*`, `summon`, `transfer`, `viewport`, …) | 37 |\n| of which: podcast verbs (`podcast-*`, `mark-for-action`) | 38 |\n| of which: conway verbs (`conway-*`, `paint-conway`) | 35 |\n| of which: grid/canvas verbs (`grid-*`, `canvas-*`, `paint-grid*`) | 33 |\n| of which: sprites kit (`flower`, `path`, `pulse`, `pixel`, `tone`, …) | 29 |\n| of which: surfaces (`paint-text`, `paint-cell`, `set-dot-*`, `clear-surface-layer`, …) | 18 |\n| of which: camera verbs (`camera-*`, `obj-get`, `grid-origin`) | 14 |\n| of which: cart-prelude (`act`, `next`, `wait`, `after`, `done`, `escalate`, `interrupted`, `invariants`, `cart`, `ctx-*`) | 12 |\n| of which: audio verbs (`audio-*`, `radio-current-*`) | 11 |\n| of which: motion verbs (`lean-aside`, `ease-aside`, `settle-breath`, `anchor-settle`, `reach`, `pluck`, `toss`, `land`) | 8 |\n| of which: scene-director verbs (`surface-fade-others`, `surface-bring-together`, `surface-restore`, `card-do`, `card-emit`) | 5 |\n| of which: widgets (`button`, `analog-pad`, `display`, `define-card`) | 4 |\n| of which: game-kit (`frame`, `key?`, `on-frame`, `stop`) | 4 |\n| of which: sakura-organize (`sakura-organize!`) | 1 |\n| of which: layout (`layout-bricklay!` — installed in index.js:232) | 1 |\n| `.sks` cart files in corpus | 270 |\n| Manifests published in production | 2 (Shop Services full · Podcasts stub) |\n| Manifests required by spec | 24+ |\n\n**Source of truth:** `Env.define(name, val, meta)` in `curator-web/src/scheme/interp.js:97-108` registers every verb into `runtime/verbRegistry.js`. The 370 figure is install-time bindings, counted from `env.define(...)` + base.js `def(...)` sites.\n\n---\n\n## §1. Manifest of every verb Sakura can reach\n\nVerbs are grouped by their installer. Each group's perm-class + binding status came from SCHEME-INVENTORY §3 (the deep dispatch-time audit).\n\n### §1.1 Substrate + math + list + string + predicate (base.js · 117)\n\nThe floor every cart writes against. Bound at every entry point (`run`, `runProgram`, `runSurface`, `runWithCards`, `dispatchScheme`). All declared `perm: 'read'` via the `def()` helper — correct, since these are pure compute.\n\nNotable: `=?` (PICO-8-style DWIM equal), `round2` (money-friendly), `cagr` / `margin` / `markup` / `markdown` / `profit` / `fee` / `net` / `pct-change` (finance kit), `above?` / `below?` / `crossed?` (threshold helpers), `dist` / `near?` / `in-rect?` / `overlap?` (game-kit geometry).\n\n### §1.2 Paint Kit (paint/index.js → installPaintKit · 29 primitives)\n\nAll 29 bound at `paint` perm via `defaultMetaFor` regex `/^paint-/`. Verified correct.\n\n**Substrate (4):** `paint-dots` · `paint-text` · `paint-marquee` · `paint-clear`\n**Geometry (6):** `paint-rect` · `paint-line` · `paint-arc` · `paint-circle` · `paint-spiral` · `paint-pipe`\n**Semantic glyphs (6):** `paint-arrow` · `paint-point-at` · `paint-heart` · `paint-star` · `paint-highlight` · `paint-surround`\n**Animated (6):** `paint-flow` · `paint-glow` · `paint-twinkle` · `paint-pulse` · `paint-fireworks` · `paint-burst`\n**Emoji (1):** `paint-emoji`\n**Procedural / TouchDesigner-class (6):** `paint-mesh` · `paint-displace` · `paint-field` · `paint-noise` · `paint-particles` · `paint-trail`\n\nRealisation depth: 5 fully realised (`paint-pipe`, `paint-mesh`, `paint-fireworks`, `paint-burst`, `paint-field`/`paint-noise`); ~18 stubs whose Scheme-side signature is correct but whose JS-side `gfx.<op>(…)` target is incomplete (Phase B renderer). Honest read per SCHEME-INVENTORY §2.7: **interface uniformity is real; rendering depth is uneven.**\n\n### §1.3 Scene verbs (surface/scheme-host/sceneVerbs.js · 5)\n\n`surface-fade-others` · `surface-bring-together` · `surface-restore` (all `state-change`) · `card-do` (`state-change`) · `card-emit` (`paint`).\n\n**Cleanest installer in the system** — every verb meta-declared. The Transfer scene wire is complete on the verb side.\n\n### §1.4 Card verbs (cardVerbs.js · 37)\n\nIncludes the gold-standard high-perm trio: `transfer` (destructive + confirm + 1/30s rate-limit), `remove-shop` (destructive + confirm + 1/30s), `store-listing-set-price` (financial + confirm + 5/min). Plus `store-listing-republish` (destructive + confirm + 1/30s).\n\nState-change verbs explicitly declared: `card-set!`, `card-open`, `card-open-then`, `card-close`, `card-focus!`, `card-unfocus!`, `move-card`, `card-move!`, `set-active-shop`, `add-shop`, `list-item-pluck`, `list-item-toss`, `summon`.\n\nRead verbs (explicit allowlist): `card-list`, `card-kinds`, `card-kind`, `card-id-of`, `card-find-by-kind`, `card-get`, `card-rect`, `card-canvas-rect`, `card-screen-rect`, `card-visible?`, `card-where`, `card-each`, `viewport`, `viewport-width`.\n\n**4 misclassified (perm-drift):** `cards-list` (rich-row), `after-frame`, `scale-card`, `pin-card`. All are inferred `read` but are semantically state-change or scheduling. **Punch list item D-1.**\n\n### §1.5 Motion verbs (motionVerbs.js · 8) — all perm-drift\n\n`lean-aside` · `ease-aside` · `settle-breath` · `anchor-settle` · `reach` · `pluck` · `toss` · `land`.\n\nAll 8 register WITHOUT a meta arg → inferred `read` (most permissive tier). They stamp CSS classes and emit `card-event` log entries — state-change behaviour. Per HS-1.0 §8.8.3 they should be `animate` perm. **Punch list item D-2.**\n\n### §1.6 Camera verbs (cameraVerbs.js · 14) — 6 perm-drift\n\nPure reads (correctly classed): `camera-state`, `camera-x`, `camera-y`, `camera-scale`, `grid-origin`, `obj-get`, `camera-trace`.\n`!`-pattern hits → state-change (correct): `camera-set!`.\n**Misclassified as `read` but animate:** `camera-pan-to`, `camera-zoom-to`, `camera-zoom-to-card`, `camera-bring-to-view`, `camera-home`, `camera-fit-all`. **Punch list item D-3.**\n\n### §1.7 Podcast verbs (podcastVerbs.js · 38) — gold standard\n\n**ALL 38 verbs have explicit perm + confirm + rateLimit + summary.** The reference installer A4 should mimic. Reads at `read`, writes at `state-change`, cart-friendly rate-limits (e.g. `60/min` for `record-mention`).\n\n### §1.8 Conway verbs (conway.js · 35) — practically inert\n\n`conway-*` verbs (counts, init, step, spawns, glows, tribes). All inferred. Most are reads; some are writes (`conway-init`, `conway-step`, `conway-spawn-*`, `conway-fire-rainbow`, `conway-soup-flush`) and don't match the state-change regex, so they're inferred `read`. **Practically:** Conway only runs inside the music card's own evaluator — not in the dispatcher path. No live risk; flag if the music card ever rewires through `runWithCards`.\n\n### §1.9 Grid / canvas verbs (grid.js · 33)\n\n`grid-*`, `canvas-*`, `paint-grid*`. Mostly correctly inferred. `grid-cell-set!` and `canvas-cell-set!` hit the `!` pattern → state-change (correct). `canvas-spawn-pattern` is misclassified as read.\n\n### §1.10 Audio verbs (audioVerbs.js · 11)\n\nAll inferred read; all genuinely read (snap-cache lookups). Correct outcome but lacks explicit declaration. **Non-blocking; recommend explicit declaration for future-proofing.**\n\n### §1.11 Widgets (widgets.js · 4)\n\n`button` · `analog-pad` · `display` (all pure constructors, correctly inferred read) · `define-card` (misclassified — registers a new card kind into the dynamic-card registry; semantically state-change). **Punch list item D-4.**\n\n### §1.12 Layout + organize (2)\n\n`layout-bricklay!` (state-change via `!` pattern) · `sakura-organize!` (explicit state-change). Correct.\n\n### §1.13 Game-kit (gameKit.js · 4) and sprites (sprites.js · 29)\n\n`frame`, `key?`, `on-frame`, `stop` (game-kit). 29 sprite verbs (`flower`, `path`, `pulse`, `pixel`, `tone`, `viewport`, `mic-*`, …). Music-card-only; not on dispatcher path.\n\n### §1.14 Cart-prelude (cartPrelude.js · 12)\n\n`cart`, `invariants`, `next`, `done`, `escalate`, `wait`, `after`, `interrupted`, `act`, `ctx-get`, `ctx-set`, `ctx-result`. **These are NOT bound in the `runWithCards` env by default** — they're a separate ABI (the 225 etsy descriptor-carts use them via `cartDriver.js`). Sakura, going through `dispatchScheme`, cannot see these names. See §3 below.\n\n### §1.15 Surfaces (surfaces.js · 18) — installed only by runSurface\n\n`paint-text` (older shape), `paint-cell`, `paint-dots` (older shape), `rasterize-text`, `dot-count`, `set-dot-alpha`, `set-dot-color`, `set-dot-radius`, `begin-frame`, `end-frame`, `clear-surface-layer`, `age-layer`, `svg-set`, `surface-exists?`, `grid-cols`, `grid-rows`, `register-tick`, `cancel-tick`. **Effectively dead from the dispatcher path** — `runWithCards` doesn't install them.\n\n### §1.16 Shop Services manifest verbs (shopServicesManifest.js · 37 declared, 1 bound)\n\nManifest declares 37 verbs across `BASE_SERVICES` (12) + `L1_PLUS_SERVICES` (9) + `THIRD_PARTY_SERVICES` (12) + 4 engine verbs. **Only `transfer` is bound** in the registry (via `cardVerbs.js`). The other 36 return `unknown-verb` on dispatch. `installShopServicesVerbs` is referenced in a comment (shopServicesManifest.js:291) but **does not exist**. **Punch list item B-3 (BLOCKER).**\n\n### §1.17 Shop platform verbs (shopVerbs.js) — installed nowhere\n\n`installShopVerbs` exists but is **never called** in `runWithCards`/`dispatchScheme`/`runProgram`. The 225 etsy carts survive because they use the descriptor ABI (`act 'etsy/listings …`) which the cart-driver loop handles separately. **Confirmed orphan; remove from the runtime tree or wire it in — Architect decision.**\n\n---\n\n## §2. Drift table — verbs with mismatched perm + bindings declared-but-missing\n\n| # | Verb / installer | Drift | Fix tier | Source |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `lean-aside`, `ease-aside`, `settle-breath`, `anchor-settle`, `reach`, `pluck`, `toss`, `land` (motionVerbs.js × 8) | Inferred `read`; should be `animate` per HS-1.0 §8.8.3 | Add `{perm: 'animate'}` to each `env.define` | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.1 |\n| 2 | `camera-pan-to`, `camera-zoom-to`, `camera-zoom-to-card`, `camera-bring-to-view`, `camera-home`, `camera-fit-all` (cameraVerbs.js × 6) | Inferred `read`; should be `animate` | Add `{perm: 'animate'}` | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.5 |\n| 3 | `cards-list`, `after-frame`, `scale-card`, `pin-card` (cardVerbs.js × 4) | Inferred `read`; semantically `state-change` (cards-list is a debatable read; rest are state) | Add explicit perm per verb | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.2 |\n| 4 | `define-card` (widgets.js × 1) | Inferred `read`; registers a new card kind into a global registry — state-change | Add `{perm: 'state-change'}` | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.10 |\n| 5 | All surface verbs (`set-dot-alpha`, `set-dot-color`, `set-dot-radius`, `begin-frame`, `end-frame`, `paint-cell`, `age-layer`, `clear-surface-layer`, `svg-set`, `register-tick`, `cancel-tick`) | Inferred `read`; only installed by `runSurface` (legacy path); not on dispatcher | Add explicit perms IF/when wired to dispatcher | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.9 |\n| 6 | All audio verbs × 11 | Inferred `read`; actually read — outcome correct, declaration missing | Add explicit `{perm: 'read'}` for future-proofing | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.7 |\n| 7 | Conway state-change verbs (`conway-init`, `conway-step`, `conway-spawn-*`, `conway-fire-rainbow`, `conway-soup-flush`, `conway-end-round`) | Inferred `read`; semantically state-change | If music card moves through dispatcher, add `{perm: 'state-change'}` | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.11 |\n| 8 | **`receive-listing` (TRANSFER-SEMANTICS §2)** | Manifest declares it / cart calls it; **no binding in registry; no manifest declares it on shop-explorer** | Bind via new `shopExplorerManifest.js`; stub returning `['ok', {alreadyReceived:true,…}]` | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.15, §8.1 B-1 |\n| 9 | **`release-listing` (TRANSFER-SEMANTICS §3)** | Required for move-semantic transfer; no binding; no cart calls it yet | Same path as #8 | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.15 |\n| 10 | **`read-inventory` (shop-explorer)** — cart calls it | No manifest declaration; no binding | A3/A4 manifest sweep | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.15 |\n| 11 | **`set-inventory`, `create-listing-from`, `set-processing-time`, `set-vacation-mode`** (shop-explorer × 4) | Same shape as #10 | A3/A4 manifest sweep | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.15 |\n| 12 | **Shop Services manifest declares 37 verbs → only `transfer` bound** | 36 of 37 return `unknown-verb` on dispatch | `installShopServicesVerbs` (B-3) | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.13, §8.1 B-3 |\n| 13 | 22 card-kinds with renderer registration but no manifest registration | Per-card `(card-do \"#card/<kind>\" 'anything …)` rejects on every call | A3 manifest sweep | SCHEME-INVENTORY §5 |\n| 14 | `validateRegistry({throwOnFail: false})` (dispatch.js:60) | Substrate critic CRITICAL — drift warnings silent, don't block boot | Flip to true at v2.20.0 close after fixes #1-#4 | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.16, §8.1 B-4 |\n\n**Total drift count: 14 categories, ~60 individual verbs.** Most are tier-misclassification (low-risk for Sakura since she's a higher tier than untrusted; high-risk if/when an untrusted callsite emerges). Two are BLOCKER for v2.20.0 (#8, #12).\n\n---\n\n## §3. The two-ABI honesty — the Sakura-reach gap\n\nSakura speaks Scheme through the **`dispatchScheme` chokepoint**, which uses `runWithCards`. That env installs ~80 verbs Sakura can call: 29 paint primitives + 5 scene verbs + 8 motion verbs + 14 camera verbs + 37 card verbs + scene-director + organize/layout + a few audio/podcast. Plus the 117 base verbs (math/list/string/predicate).\n\nShe **CANNOT** reach:\n- The 12 cart-prelude verbs (`act`, `next`, `wait`, …) — descriptor ABI only, install requires `installCartPrelude` (cartDriver.js).\n- The ~200 platform verbs in `shopVerbs.js` (`etsy/listings`, `etsy/publish`, `ebay/inventory-items`, …) — installer is dead code on dispatcher path.\n- The 36 unbound Shop Services verbs (`reprice`, `crosspost`, `messages`, …) — declared in manifest, never bound.\n- The 7 missing per-card verbs (`receive-listing`, `release-listing`, `read-inventory`, `set-inventory`, `create-listing-from`, `set-processing-time`, `set-vacation-mode`) — manifest-promised, not declared on any card, not bound.\n- The 225 descriptor-style etsy carts (`carts/etsy/*.sks`) — they don't go through `dispatchScheme` at all.\n\n**Sakura's reachable surface today = ~80 verbs + paint kit. Her promised surface (post-v2.20.0 A3+A4+S5b) = ~150 verbs. The training corpus must reflect the *current* reachable set, not the manifest's promise.**\n\n---\n\n## §4. Manual drift — `/documents/scheme-manual` vs reality\n\nSource: `curator-web/src/scheme/SPEC.md` (engine spec) + the manual rendered at `/documents/scheme-manual`.\n\n| Manual section | Manual state | Reality | Drift |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Math/list/string/predicate primitives | Documents most of base.js | 117 verbs in base.js | Some gaps (e.g. `cagr`, `pct-change`, `round2`, `crossed?` not in manual; `every`/`any`/`take`/`drop`/`zip` partial) |\n| Paint Kit | Lists ~17 primitives (older snapshot) | 29 today | **Out by 12.** New since v2.19.0: `paint-line`, `paint-arc`, `paint-circle`, `paint-spiral`, `paint-pipe`, `paint-trail`, `paint-displace`, `paint-field`, `paint-noise`, `paint-particles`, `paint-mesh`, `paint-clear` |\n| Card verbs | Documents `card-list`, `card-open`, `card-close`, `card-focus!`, `transfer`, `move-card` | 37 today including `card-do`, `card-emit`, `summon`, `add-shop`, `remove-shop`, `set-active-shop`, `store-listing-set-price` etc. | **~25 verbs undocumented** |\n| Scene verbs | Not in manual | 5 verbs live (sceneVerbs.js) | **Entire scene-director surface undocumented** |\n| Motion verbs | Not in manual | 8 verbs live (motionVerbs.js) | **Entire motion surface undocumented** |\n| Camera verbs | Not in manual | 14 verbs live | **Entire camera surface undocumented** |\n| Podcast verbs | Not in manual | 38 verbs live | **Entire podcast surface undocumented** |\n| Audio verbs | Not in manual | 11 verbs live | Undocumented |\n| Conway / grid | Partial — conway-step + spawns documented | 33+35=68 verbs live | Largely undocumented |\n| Safety stars (withStars) | Documented as concept | Implementation diverged | Manual says \"8 stars\"; implementation has the pattern + perm + confirm + rateLimit + schema + tier + audit + identity + healing-chip-stub |\n| Cart-prelude (descriptor ABI) | Partially documented in AUTOMATIONS-STATE-MACHINE-CHAPTER.md | 12 verbs live in cartPrelude.js | Cross-doc; the manual + chapter don't reconcile |\n\n**Verdict:** The manual covers ~40% of the live verb surface. **Update is overdue but not blocking** — the manual is operator-facing reference, and the operator-driven entry path (Automation Studio) reads verb meta from the live registry. The training corpus, however, MUST use the live registry as ground truth, not the manual.\n\n---\n\n## §5. Cart corpus health — 270 `.sks` files\n\n| Bucket | Count | ABI | Live? |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| etsy/*.sks | 225 | descriptor (`cartDriver.js`) | Yes — driven by the 225-cart manifest |\n| etsy/_reference/* | ~12 | reference | No (safe-versions + ml fixtures) |\n| google/*.sks | 6 | descriptor | Yes |\n| scenes/*.sks | 12 | sync `dispatchScheme` | Yes (incl. `transfer-shop-to-shop.sks`, `sync-inventory.sks`, `crosspost-listing.sks`, `bulk-readiness.sks`, `bulk-shipping.sks`, `bulk-markdown.sks`, `vacation-mode.sks`, `reconcile-sold.sks`, `returns-center.sks`, `messages-inbox.sks`, `email-inbox.sks`, `free-shipping-standard.sks`) |\n| transfer/*.sks | 3 | descriptor (`transfer-common.sks`, `etsy-to-ebay-transfer.sks`, `ebay-to-etsy-transfer.sks`) | Yes (deep per-listing path; merge-vs-keep-separate decision pending per TRANSFER-SEMANTICS.md §10.6) |\n| layout/*.sks | 1 | sync (`bricklay.sks`) | Yes |\n| music/*.sks | 2 | sync via `runProgram` (`conway.sks` + petals source) | Yes |\n| rules/*.sks | (small) | descriptor helpers | reference |\n\n**All 12 scene carts share the same gap:** they use `(card-do <addr> '<verb>)` for the real work; the target verbs aren't declared on any manifest; the destination card has no runtime binding. **Cards-critique finding #2 + #5 are still current.**\n\n---\n\n## §6. New primitives needed for v0.6 / v0.7\n\nSorted by ROI (highest first). The basis for this list is the corpus's actual call patterns + SCHEME-INVENTORY §8.\n\n### §6.1 Critical (unblock operators / cart authors)\n\n| Verb | Why | Source |\n|---|---|---|\n| `string-split`, `string-trim`, `string-upcase`, `string-downcase`, `string-contains?`, `string-replace`, `string-join`, `string-pad` | 22 L0 normalization carts (`fix-punctuation.sks`, `singularize.sks`, `titlecase-this.sks`, `normalize-currency-format.sks`, …) currently dispatch to L0 because Scheme has no string ops. Add ~8 SRFI-13 essentials and they run locally. | SCHEME-INVENTORY §1.5, §8.2 C-1 |\n| `symbol?`, `procedure?`, `pair?`, `list?`, `integer?`, `vector?` | Type-dispatching impossible past number/string/boolean; pattern-match style code blocked. | SCHEME-INVENTORY §1.3 |\n| `receive-listing`, `release-listing` (verbs + manifest on shop-explorer) | Transfer scene plays animation, no listings actually move. The centerpiece demo is a lie until this lands. | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.15, §8.1 B-1 |\n| `installShopServicesVerbs(env)` binding 37 verbs (stubs for 26 that don't have helpers) | Every Shop Services tile tap, except the 11 that have helpers, returns `unknown-verb`. | SCHEME-INVENTORY §3.13, §8.1 B-3 |\n| `validateManifests()` build-time check | CARD-MANIFEST-CONTRACT.md §6.5 promises it; doesn't exist. Future manifest sweeps drift silently. | SCHEME-INVENTORY §5.2, §8.2 C-2 |\n\n### §6.2 High-value (cart-author quality of life)\n\n| Verb | Why |\n|---|---|\n| `fold`, `fold-right`, `flatten`, `partition`, `unzip`, `iota` | SRFI-1 essentials; cart authors keep manually emulating. |\n| `exp`, `log`, `log10`, `ln`, `tanh`, `acos`, `asin` | Future ML-on-cart work (`l0-suggest-tags.sks`-style scoring). Currently no transcendentals beyond `expt`. |\n| `mod` (alias for `modulo`) | Standard Scheme alias; not load-bearing. |\n| `format` / `printf` | No formatted output today; `string-append` + `number->string` is the workaround. |\n| Hash table / dict primitives (`make-hash`, `hash-ref`, `hash-set!`, `hash-has?`) | Carts approximate with assoc-lists (O(n)); ugly for 12+ key plists. |\n| `paint-pipe-trace` (debug overlay) | Pipe is the gold-standard primitive but invisible when debugging; an opt-in overlay would accelerate scene authoring. |\n\n### §6.3 Engine + manifest sweep (v0.6 blocking)\n\n| Verb / surface | Need |\n|---|---|\n| 22 card-kind minimum-default manifests (CardTemplate auto-registration per CARD-MANIFEST-CONTRACT.md §8) | Today `(card-do '#card/<kind>' …)` rejects on every unmanifested card. |\n| `card-where-service`, `card-of-kind` (cards-spec verbs) | Per memory [[curator-cards-addressable-intelligent-metadata]] — 12-verb surface; today only `card-do` + `card-emit` are bound. |\n| `surface-cards`, `surface-state`, `surface-focus`, `surface-move`, `surface-trace` | Per memory [[curator-canvas-is-sakuras-home]] — the ~20 talk-tool verbs; some bound (`surface-fade-others`, `surface-bring-together`, `surface-restore`), most missing. |\n| Inter-card event-bus subscribers wired from `accepts[]` in manifests | A3 sweep — today no card subscribes via manifest; podcasts↔shop-services bus is hand-wired. |\n\n### §6.4 Polish (v0.7+)\n\n| Item | Why |\n|---|---|\n| Flatten `paint-text` / `paint-marquee` rasters to `Float32Array[N*4]` | Per-frame object reads → zero-alloc; long marquees hit ~12k reads/sec. |\n| `defaultMetaFor` patterns extended to cover state-change `*-init`, `*-step`, `*-spawn-*` | Auto-classify conway-style verbs correctly. |\n| Better error messages on `unknown-verb` rejection (did-you-mean suggestions) | Cart-author friendliness. |\n| `_internalRunWithCards` rename for `runOnSurface` | Substrate critic finding; the safe-sounding name hides a chokepoint bypass. |\n\n### §6.5 Defer to v0.8+\n\n- Full Scheme macros (`define-syntax`, `syntax-rules`, hygienic expansion). Current cart corpus uses closures + named-let; no demand.\n- A REPL surface. AutomationStudio is the closest thing.\n- Worker isolation port (B1b). Scaffolded; session-sized lift; main-thread runtime is security-correct default per HS-1.0 §8.7.\n\n---\n\n## §7. Punch list for the next training corpus\n\nThe corpus generator at `~/.forge/corpus/sakura/raw.jsonl` must include pairs covering every reachable verb. Today's pairs are weighted toward marketplace + Cortex; the engine surface is undertaught.\n\n| Corpus slice | Current pair count (est.) | Target | Gap |\n|---|---:|---:|---:|\n| Paint Kit (29 primitives × ~30-50 pairs each) | sparse | ~1,000 | per memory [[curator-first-class-graphics-primitives]] / training note #7 |\n| HelloSurface home (engine modules + 20 talk-tool verbs) | sparse | ~600 | training note #8 |\n| Inter-card API (12-verb manifest-mediated surface) | sparse | ~400 | training note #9 |\n| Scene-director carts (12 scene carts × example flows) | sparse | ~300 | NEW |\n| Motion + camera + organize verbs | sparse | ~250 | NEW |\n| Card-control composition (open/close/focus/move/summon) | partial | ~400 | NEW |\n| Error-envelope vocabulary (`unknown-verb` / `perm-denied` / `confirm-required` / `rate-limit` / `arg-shape`) | none | ~150 | NEW — Sakura must articulate dispatcher errors |\n| Cart-prelude descriptor ABI (act/next/wait/after/done) | scarce | ~250 | NEW — let her READ the 225 etsy carts even though she can't CALL them |\n| Marketplace + Cortex + persona (existing) | majority | hold | maintain |\n\n**Total new pairs needed: ~3,300.** That's a single training cadence's worth at the canonical 32k-pair scale (Sakura LLM §22).\n\n---\n\n## §8. Discipline floor — recommendations\n\n1. **Flip `validateRegistry({throwOnFail: true})`** at v2.20.0 close, after the 18 misclassified verbs land explicit perms. The validator already runs; flipping the flag turns the warning into a build break. ~10 lines + ~25 verb-meta tweaks. **Highest leverage.**\n2. **Land `validateManifests()`** alongside, cross-checking declared verbs (manifest) vs bound verbs (registry). ~40 lines. Prevents future manifest drift.\n3. **Adopt the podcast-verbs pattern as the installer template** for the 22-card manifest sweep + the 37 Shop Services bindings. Sample `env.define(name, body, {perm, confirm, rateLimit, summary})` for every verb. No more inferred perms in new code.\n4. **Rebuild the `/documents/scheme-manual`** from the live registry at build-time. The manifest already carries `summary` per verb; the manual should be generated, not hand-written. Closes the drift loop permanently.\n5. **Tag every verb with `addedIn: 'v2.X.Y'`** in its meta so the corpus generator can stratify pairs by stability — Sakura learns mature verbs first.\n\n---\n\n— Architect · 2026-06-09\n")
